brands.description: Adobe Acrobat is a family of application software and Web services developed by Adobe Systems to view, create, manipulate, print and manage files in Portable Document Format (PDF). The family comprises Acrobat Reader (formerly Adobe Reader), Acrobat (formerly Acrobat Exchange) and Acrobat.com.
brands.name: Adobe Acrobat

brands.description: VLC media player (commonly known as VLC) is a portable, free and open-source, cross-platform media player and streaming media server written by the VideoLAN project. VLC is available for desktop operating systems and mobile platforms, such as Android, iPad, iPhone, and iPod Touch. VLC is also available on App stores such as Apple's App Store.
brands.name: VLC media player

namedLocations.description: A caudex (plural: caudices) of a plant is a stem, but the term is also used to mean a rootstock and particularly a basal stem structure from which new growth arises. In the strict sense of the term, meaning a stem, "caudex" is most often used with plants that have a different stem morphology from the typical angiosperm dicotyledon stem: examples of this include palms, ferns, and cycads.
namedLocations.name: Caudex

transcript.text: Hello, welcome to the On Print Shop Designer Studio tutorial series.
In today's video, we will walk through the steps to create PDF block templates using PDF Block Generator.
This helps you to create blocks automatically in a PDF block file and reduces your work by 50%.
So let's get started.
From the admin panel, navigate to the blog generator URL and just click on the PDF Block Generator.
From the screen, click on upload file and upload the sample file over here.
Once you successfully upload the file, you can see all the block names that are in the file.
Here you can see the block name and you can change the title as you want.
For example, we are taking the name and here there is a button to include this block in the file or not.
If you want to include this block in the file, you can enable this button or else you can disable it.
Next, we have combined text flow.
If you have various blocks in the file such as name, title, e-mail or website then you can separately create the blocks into the file.
To create the separate blocks we need to disable this button and similarly we can create another block using the same process.
If you keep this enabled then it will keep taking the text flow.
So this is for the second page.
It will take the block name automatically.
Now click on the generate button to generate the file.
When you open it in Adobe Acrobat, you can see the generated PDF block file where the blocks are generated automatically only.
You need to adjust the length of the block or you can save the width of the block.
Now when you select the block and click on properties, you can see the coordinates of the block that can be verified using the TT plugin.
To verify the same, access the plugins menu from the top, click on PDFLIBTT plugin.
Then click on the top down coordinate system and check the for output coordinates in TTML.
Move to the top and select the TT tool.
Now after selecting the text you have to select TT copy and then you can paste the code into the word file where you have to find the initial name of the text you have selected.
Just above that you will see the coordinates in the displayed format which you have to convert into this format with a single space between each coordinate.
After copying this select the PDF block tool from the PDFL IB blocks.
Now go to block property and here you can replace the coordinate with this one and click on apply.
You can verify that the coordinates are adjusted and it is similar to the coordinates generated by the PDF block generator.
This is how you can generate PDF blocks and verify other blocks and verify the TT whether the coordinates are correct or not.
And there you have it.
You have successfully created the PDF block files using the PDF Block generator.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chat on on printshop.com.
Thanks for tuning in.
